{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nProvision the auto-lander bot's Gerrit credential and the access right it needs to rebase changes on behalf of their uploader ŌĆö reusing the project's existing ACL machinery, without a redundant grant or an IAM change. Split out of S5 (`perpetual-ultrasonic-raccoon`).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/terraform/ssm.tf` ŌĆö EDIT: add `/rebar/prod/autolander-gerrit-token` to the existing `local.rebar_secret_params` set (the `for_each` `aws_ssm_parameter` resource with `ignore_changes = [value]` + CHANGEME sentinel), NOT a standalone resource.\n- `infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh` ŌĆö EDIT: add the mapping `autolander-gerrit-token ŌåÆ AUTOLANDER_GERRIT_TOKEN`, materialized into the SAME shared `.env` (distinct env-var from the review-bot's `GERRIT_BOT_TOKEN`).\n- `infra/gerrit/project.config` + `infra/gerrit/setup-project.sh` ŌĆö EDIT: grant the bot the **Rebase** access right (and the rebase-on-behalf-of-uploader form) on the `rebar` project's `refs/heads/*`. This lives in the **rebar project's own** `refs/meta/config` (managed here), NOT `All-Projects`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] **Credential:** the Gerrit HTTP token is an SSM **SecureString** at `/rebar/prod/autolander-gerrit-token` ŌĆö inside the existing `parameter/rebar/prod/*` prefix the EC2 instance-role IAM policy (`iam.tf` `ssm_params_read`) already grants, so **NO IAM change** (`iam.tf` read-only/unchanged; a `/rebar/autolander/*` path would fall outside the grant). Added via the `ssm.tf` `for_each` set; fetched by `fetch-secrets.sh` using **`get_param` (required/fail-fast ŌĆö NOT `get_param_optional`)** so a missing token aborts boot rather than silently producing a blank env-var, into the shared `.env` as `AUTOLANDER_GERRIT_TOKEN`; never inlined.\n- [ ] **Submit is already covered ŌĆö do NOT add a submit grant.** `RebarBotNava` is already in the `Contributors` group (`setup-project.sh` default `CONTRIBUTOR_MEMBERS`), which holds `Submit` on `refs/heads/*`. An All-Projects submit grant would be **eclipsed** anyway: `project.config` sets `exclusiveGroupPermissions = submit`, so Gerrit ignores inherited submit for that ref. AC = *verify* `RebarBotNava Ōłł Contributors` (so `POST /submit` does not 403); no new submit ACL.\n- [ ] **Rebase-on-behalf access right (concrete):** grant the **`Rebase`** access right (project.config `[access]` token **`rebase`**, confirmed in this instance's `access-control.html`) to group **`Contributors`** on the `rebar` project's `refs/heads/*` ŌĆö added to the **rebar project's** `refs/meta/config` via `setup-project.sh`/`project.config` (NOT `All-Projects`, NOT a global `[capability]`, NOT the `[submit] rebaseOnBehalfOfUploader` submit-strategy setting). Concrete stanza: `[access \"refs/heads/*\"] rebase = group Contributors`. The **on-behalf** half needs no extra grant: `rebase_on_behalf_of_uploader` checks push/upload against the *original uploader*, who already holds it (they created the change). (The bot is already a submitter via Contributors, and \"submitters can always rebase\" per the ACL docs, so this explicit `rebase` grant is belt-and-suspenders for the REST path.)\n- [ ] **Fallback protocol (no silent failure):** the AC3 smoke test is the checkpoint ŌĆö if the live rebase-on-behalf call 403s despite the `rebase` grant, the 403 body names the missing right; the documented remediation is to add exactly that named right to the same `refs/heads/*` stanza. The plan does NOT proceed to production on a 403.\n- [ ] **Tests (AC3):** `setup-project.sh` remains idempotent (re-run is a no-op); a smoke check on the live instance creates a **synthetic throwaway change on a scratch ref** (e.g. `refs/for/refs/heads/scratch-autolander`), confirms the token materializes into `.env`, that `RebarBotNava` authenticates + rebases it on-behalf (asserting the uploader is preserved) + submits it, then **abandons/cleans up the scratch change** ŌĆö never touching a real change."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783838782219356001,"uuid":"42676259-7ef7-4e86-87aa-4a8f15c8e067"}